      • getRandomSample

        java.lang.Float getRandomSample()
        Gets the value of the randomSample property. A floating point value between zero (result entity is never included) and 1 (result entity is always included) used to sample or filter results. Cannot be used with with (potentially) many types of predicates depending on the restrictions within the underlying data store.
        Returns:
        possible object is Float
